---

at first i thought it would be easier to try to decrypt the full version string at the end of python script.
the function that decrypts the full version needs a key to do it's job, obviously.
and the key had to be validated by check_key().
if you look at the function you can see it is comparing the input key with the flag.
but how?
most of the flag is set as a constant variable.

--------
key_part_static1_trial = "picoCTF{1n_7h3_|<3y_of_"
--------

and this is where the key validator ensures that the input is indeed the key AKA flag.

-----------
def check_key(key, username_trial):

    global key_full_template_trial

    if len(key) != len(key_full_template_trial):
        return False
    else:
        # Check static base key part --v
        i = 0
        for c in key_part_static1_trial:
            if key[i] != c:
                return False

            i += 1

        # TODO : test performance on toolbox container
        # Check dynamic part --v
        if key[i] != hashlib.sha256(username_trial).hexdigest()[4]:
            return False
        else:
            i += 1

        if key[i] != hashlib.sha256(username_trial).hexdigest()[5]:
            return False
        else:
            i += 1

        if key[i] != hashlib.sha256(username_trial).hexdigest()[3]:
            return False
        else:
            i += 1

        if key[i] != hashlib.sha256(username_trial).hexdigest()[6]:
            return False
        else:
            i += 1

        if key[i] != hashlib.sha256(username_trial).hexdigest()[2]:
            return False
        else:
            i += 1

        if key[i] != hashlib.sha256(username_trial).hexdigest()[7]:
            return False
        else:
            i += 1

        if key[i] != hashlib.sha256(username_trial).hexdigest()[1]:
            return False
        else:
            i += 1

        if key[i] != hashlib.sha256(username_trial).hexdigest()[8]:
            return False



        return True
-----------


and since we talked about the most of the flag bein set as a variable we can break the function in two main
parts : 
1_comparing the input with the variable set in the script
2_comparing with home hash that we don't know the input of

username_trial is also a variable set in the script.
----
username_trial = "FRASER"
----

so we got a constant hash and we can easily see what are the i'th characters of it and append them to the flag.

picoCTF{1n_7h3_|<3y_of_ac73dc29}
